        <p>
            Gas, parking, meals, and sometimes overnight stays pile up quickly. For families already
            stretched thin, these expenses can force impossible decisions. Parents skip meals to pay
            for gas. Siblings stay with relatives for days at a time. Medical debt grows alongside
            the fear and exhaustion of caring for a sick child.
        </p>

        <div class="quote-box">
            "No parent should have to choose between putting gas in the car to get their child to
            treatment and putting food on the table for their family."
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Mission & Vision -->
    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Our Mission & Vision</h2>
        <p>
            The Central Utah Tree Festival exists for one purpose: to ensure that every child in
            Sanpete County can access the specialized medical care they need, regardless of their
            family's financial circumstances.
        </p>

        <h3>What We Do</h3>
        <p>
            We provide direct financial assistance to families traveling to Primary Children's Hospital
            for their child's medical care. Our support covers the practical costs that insurance
            doesn't: gas for the long drive, parking fees at the hospital, meals during all-day
            appointments, and lodging when overnight stays are necessary.
        </p>
        <p>
            Every dollar we raise goes directly to helping families. We're an entirely volunteer-run
            organization, which means 100% of donations support the families who need it most.
        </p>

        <h3>How We Work</h3>
        <p>
            Families can apply for support through a simple, confidential process. We work quickly to
            provide assistance when it's needed most—because we know that medical needs don't wait.
        </p>

        <h3>Our Vision for the Future</h3>
        <p>
            We envision a community where no family faces the journey to specialized care alone. Where
            neighbors support neighbors. Where financial barriers never stand between a child and the
            treatment they need. And where an annual celebration of creativity and generosity reminds
            us all of what we can accomplish together.
        </p>
    </section>

